<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:35:34 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>大脑是一台模拟计算机吗？意识作为动态脑电波组织|厄尔·米勒</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/is-the-brain-an-analog-computer-consciousness-as-dynamic-brainwave-organization-earl-miller</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:35:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/is-the-brain-an-analog-computer-consciousness-as-dynamic-brainwave-organization-earl-miller</guid></item><item><title>偷走无限的人</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/the-man-who-stole-infinity</link><description>1874 年，德国数学家格奥尔格·康托 (Georg Cantor) 发表了一篇开创性的论文，表明无穷大有不同的大小，这一结果从根本上改变了数学，将无穷大视为一个具体的数学概念，而不仅仅是一个哲学思想。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-man-who-stole-infinity.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:20:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/the-man-who-stole-infinity</guid></item><item><title>摘要：艾米丽·古铁雷斯-莫顿</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/abstract-emily-gutierrez-morton</link><description>Yanchang Wang 及其同事（佛罗里达州立大学）表明，在酵母中，polo 样激酶 Cdc5 促进 SUMO 蛋白酶 Ulp2 的磷酸化，降低其对 SUMO 链的亲和力，从而促进多 SUMO 化。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract82.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:05:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/abstract-emily-gutierrez-morton</guid></item><item><title>摘要：我们能否更早地识别接受乳房植入物重建的患者的感染情况？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/abstract-can-we-identify-infections-earlier-in-patients-undergoing-breast-implant-reconstruction</link><description>Jeffrey P. Henderson 使用植入后引流液的代谢组学分析，揭示了与感染相关的分子特征，在纵向样本中，该分子特征基本上早于临床感染诊断。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract82.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 11:50:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/abstract-can-we-identify-infections-earlier-in-patients-undergoing-breast-implant-reconstruction</guid></item><item><title>结构化环境中的上下文相关适应</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/context-dependent-adaptation-in-structured-environments</link><description>抽象的。适应性进化通常会导致生态位专业化，但新生态位的成功殖民既取决于生态环境，也取决于生态环境。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/context-dependent-adaptation-in-structured-environments.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 11:35:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/context-dependent-adaptation-in-structured-environments</guid></item><item><title>免疫细胞选择性地从垂死的细胞核中提取DNA，揭示了一个被称为核细胞增多症的过程</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/immune-cells-selectively-pull-dna-from-dying-nuclei-revealing-a-process-dubbed-nucleocytosis</link><description>多年来，细胞生物学已经详细描述了细胞如何划分其内部功能。该组织的核心是细胞核，它容纳遗传物质，并通过坚固的核膜与细胞质分开。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/immune-cells-selectively-pull-dna-from-dying-nuclei-revealing-a-process-dubbed-nucleocytosis2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 11:20:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/immune-cells-selectively-pull-dna-from-dying-nuclei-revealing-a-process-dubbed-nucleocytosis</guid></item><item><title>Slit-Robo 排斥和 neurturin-Gfrα 吸引力的时空协调引导视网膜分层过程中的多极迁移</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/spatiotemporal-coordination-of-slit-robo-repulsion-and-neurturin-gfr%ce%b1-attraction-guides-multipolar-migration-during-retinal-lamination</link><description>莱赫蒂马基等人。揭示了排斥性 Slit1b/2-Robo2 和有吸引力的 neurturin-Gfrα1/2-Ret 信号如何共同协调水平细胞在脊椎动物视网膜拥挤、无支架环境中的多极迁移。这项工作是通过复杂的转录组学分析、靶向 F0 CRISPR 筛选以及 3D 固定和实时成像来实现的。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/spatiotemporal-coordination-of-slit-robo-repulsion-and-neurturin-gfrceb1-attraction-guides-multipolar-migration-during-retinal-lamination2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 11:05:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/spatiotemporal-coordination-of-slit-robo-repulsion-and-neurturin-gfr%ce%b1-attraction-guides-multipolar-migration-during-retinal-lamination</guid></item><item><title>可以训练大脑类器官来解决目标导向的任务</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/brain-organoids-can-be-trained-to-solve-a-goal-directed-task</link><description>这项研究是实验室培养的大脑类器官中目标导向学习的首次严格学术论证，并为自适应类器官计算奠定了基础——探索实验室培养的大脑类器官学习和解决任务的能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-organoids-can-be-trained-to-solve-a-goal-directed-task2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 10:50:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/brain-organoids-can-be-trained-to-solve-a-goal-directed-task</guid></item><item><title>肿瘤-免疫-神经回路破坏癌症恶病质的能量稳态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/tumor-immune-neural-circuit-disrupts-energy-homeostasis-in-cancer-cachexia</link><description>癌症恶病质中的肿瘤免疫神经回路。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/tumor-immune-neural-circuit-disrupts-energy-homeostasis-in-cancer-cachexia2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 10:35:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/tumor-immune-neural-circuit-disrupts-energy-homeostasis-in-cancer-cachexia</guid></item><item><title>当我们学习时，神经元接收精确定制的教学信号</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/neurons-receive-precisely-tailored-teaching-signals-as-we-learn</link><description>大脑如何知道在学习过程中需要调整哪些神经元以优化行为？麻省理工学院的研究人员发现，大脑可以使用逐个细胞的错误信号来做到这一点——与通过反向传播训练人工智能系统的方式惊人地相似。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neurons-receive-precisely-tailored-teaching-signals-as-we-learn2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 10:20:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/02/neurons-receive-precisely-tailored-teaching-signals-as-we-learn</guid></item></channel></rss>